epochs.name: Screening/Prospective Observational Phase
epochs.description: 4-week phase to confirm non-response to current oral antidepressant.

epochs.name: Open-label Induction Phase
epochs.description: 4-week phase where subjects receive esketamine plus a new oral antidepressant.

epochs.name: Optimization Phase
epochs.description: 12-week phase to stabilize response/remission and determine dosing frequency.

epochs.name: Maintenance Phase
epochs.description: Double-blind phase where stable remitters/responders are randomized to continue esketamine or switch to placebo.

epochs.name: Follow-up Phase
epochs.description: Phase following the last dose of study medication.
